- Easy to use

title: Why Toy Unboxing and Other Kid Videos Get So Many Views Explained
tags: So many views,Explained,Toy Channels,Toys,Toy,VanDeGraph,Analysis,Data Science,Youtube Explained,Finger Family,Playing with toys,Ryan ToysReview,Toy Videos,Suprise Eggs,Toy Monster,Nursery Rhymes,views,so popular,billion views,millions of views,why does this have so many views,toy freaks,toy review,toy channels viewbotting,why do toy videos get so many views,why does this video have so many views,why do videos for kids get millions of views,toy channel
description:
Toy Unboxings and other kid videos like Nursery Rhymes like the Finger Family or live action skits with characters such as Elsa and Spiderman are a very weird class of videos on youtube. They can sometimes get hundreds of millions of views and it seems pretty baffling, but even this phenomena can be explained.

Some channels that are really successful and get billions of views are Ryan ToysReview,  LittleBabyBum, Toy Monster, Toy Freaks, and  Masha and the Bear. 

These channels are getting billions of views spread out among there many videos, many of which are pretty indistinguishable from one another. Their best videos get hundreds of millions of views, but often there are so many dislikes on these videos. 

In order to understand why kid videos get so many views you need to realize that there are millions of kids on youtube swiping around randomly and they don't use the website like adults. They will click things by accident and have short attention spans which means they click on even more videos than adults. 

In the video I go over much of the data I collected which confirms that kid views last much less time than regular views, and I also expose the fact that these toy channels are doing the best on youtube since they are the channels gaining the most amount of views per month, even more than channels with lots of subscribers. 

If you are looking to start a toy channel for some reason, this video could also be for you since I go into what makes a toy channel successful and how you could get the youtube algorithms to work for you. This was not the purpose of the video but while making it I realized that some of this could be good advice for running a toy channel. 


If you've ever wondered why do toy videos get so many views then this is the video for you.

Article I wrote an article that covers stuff I left out of the video:

https://medium.com/@vandegraph/why-toy-videos-get-hundreds-of-millions-of-views-on-youtube-explained-da6629ac88fa#.lr6wpchym

More Youtube Analysis from someone else, worth the read: https://artoftroubleshooting.com/2015/11/04/tube-of-plenty-analyzing-youtubes-first-decade/

Why Gaming Channels are so popular by MatPat: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EgMqhEMhVV8

Difference between San Francisco, Silicon Valley, and the Bay Area Explained: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KWrLj0f4Dgc

description:
CHUGGINGTON MEGA BLOKS Jet Pack Adventure - Unboxing and Review - 4 Layout Demo

Blast-off to hours of chuggersonic adventure with Wilson and Action Chugger in this fast-paced CHUGGINGTON MEGA BLOKS Jet Pack Adventure Set! See Action Chugger and Wilson fly down the buildable sky-rail with their jet packs to see who will land first. Build and rebuild the iconic Clock Tower and Chuggington depo for loads of exciting action. Build the tracks through the buildings & ride the rails up to four levels high. With over 103 buildable pieces included in the set, the building possibilities are endless!    Combine with other Chuggington Mega Bloks characters and play sets to multiply the fun!

- Includes 4-part buildable Vee and 2 Chuggers: 8-part buildable Wilson and Action Chugger, both with mouth-movement for lots of fun!
- Cool buildable Jet-Pack for the Chuggers to fly through the customizable Sky-Rail!
- 2-in-1 Build and rebuild possibilities with a 4-storey Clock Tower and a 3-level train station!
- Build lots of different track configurations included in the playset!
- Hours of fun on its own or with other Mega Bloks Chuggington Construction sets.

Sells for US$45 - US$50 at Amazon, Walmart

description:
Lego Friends Heartlake Airport Set 41109, released mid-2015 features a passenger jet, this is very exciting! I love taking the top off and arranging the passengers (all three of them) for takeoff. There's a little onboard toilet and a baggage hold and a snack trolley and reclining chairs, and a proper airplane door that opens and shuts just like a real one! You can arrange the pilot and co-pilot in the cockpit simply by removing the roof. Check out all the specs below, the airport itself is fun, but the airplane has the most play potential (at my house, anyway!). Prepare for takeoff!

Jet off on an exciting vacation with Heartlake Airlines! Help Stephanie check in her luggage at the LEGO¬Æ Friends Airport and place it on the turning carousel while flight attendant Sandra gives her the boarding pass. Then head to the duty free store to buy some perfume and go upstairs to the cafeteria while you wait for the flight to be called. Then it‚Äôs time to board the big plane! Place the rolling staircase at the airplane door and help Stephanie find her reclining seat while the luggage isloaded in the back of the plane. Make the final cockpit checks before takeoff with David the pilot, and once you‚Äôre flying high, prepare freshly made coffees and snacks in the galley with Sandra. Then push the trolley down the aisle to serve the passengers. Settle down with Stephanie to watch a movie while she enjoys her meal and then freshen up in the bathroom before everyone takes their seats for a smooth landing. Includes 3 mini-doll figures: Stephanie, pilot David and flight attendant Sandra.

Includes 3 mini-doll figures: Stephanie, pilot David and flight attendant Sandra
Features an opening airplane, rolling staircase and an airport building
Airplane features real-plane-style opening doors; cockpit with control panel and levers; cabin with 3 reclining seats and a TV element; kitchen area with coffee machine, opening fridge, announcement phone and folding seat elements; bathroom with opening door, toilet, sink and occupancy indicator element; and a luggage compartment
Airportbuilding features a check-in desk, turning carousel, duty free shop and an upstairs cafeteria
Accessory elements include a flight attendant‚Äôs trolley, tray, fruits, cookies, soda can, milk, coffee cups, glass, croissant, bottles of perfume and cream, hair accessories, candy boxes, 2 pairs of sunglasses, 3 pieces of luggage and ski equipment
Lift the entire roof off the airplane for easy play inside!
Check in the luggage on the turning carousel

Help David announce take-off as the airplane taxis to the runway
Serve food and drinks to all the passengers with Sandra
Enjoy a movie on the TV then freshen up in the bathroom before landing

Product description: This unique snap-together fashion kit comes with 260 pieces of funny jewelry beads in various shapes, sizes, designs, colors. Stimulate creativity Skills Do it by yourselves, make a beautiful decoration and puts you in a good happy mood. Girls snap the beads cultivate their hand-eye cooperation skill. Easy Snap Design for ages 3 and up. Beads are connected by insert. It is simple and convenient to disassemble and assemble. These beads are made from Recycled Toys Perfect for parties, rainy days, or just having fun at the house, you can be with this fully reusable jewelry kit. Make it, wear it, remake it, and wear it again. BPA Free, The toy beads are sturdy and well-made, it is non-toxic. Best gift for girls beading and jewelry making,also a good idea for birthday and Chritsmas gift.
Review by Davna (mom)- Once I received this DIY jewelry making kit I first looked at the packaging and I really like that it came in a plastic jar container that is really easy to open and close for Tiffany. The beads themselves are actually very well made, the quality  feels like beads that you would find at the Lakeshore Learning Store (except for HALF the price!) I love that the beads come in different textures, sizes and vibrant colors. It comes with a little booklet with pictures of some of the jewelry you can create which Tiffany liked to look at and recreated some of those accessories. The main thing I love about this toy is that it actually keeps both my girls entertained for LONG periods of time and it allows for their creativity to shine. We also use these to do some math, count and even create patterns! This is NOT meant for children under 3 as there are many small chocking hazard pieces BUT my youngest enjoys playing with them too under my CAREFUL supervision. It has been over a week now since we received this toy and since then both my girls have been playing with them DAILY! I highly recommend! 
CONS- The only con I found about this product is that some beads are harder to connect than others. Tiffany will be playing and be so nice and focused but then will have to come to me from time to time to help her snap some beads together which disrupts her (working) playtime. Tiffany is 4 years old so I know as she gets bigger she will be stronger and it will be easier for her to do completely on her own but if you have a 3 year old you will most likely have to play with them to help. My two year old already figured out which beads are harder to connect so she makes sure to only play with the beads that are easier to use lol

In the olden days, kids raced one other using turtles scooped out of a pond or paper boats made out of their younger brother‚Äôs birth certificate. The Techno Gears Marble Mania Dual Speedway hosts race after thrilling race without requiring kids to leave the basement. Young racers launch their marble into a tubular speedway, waving crumpled dollar bills as their orb plummets past panoplies of breakneck turns and moveable contraptions. Hundreds of colorful pieces comprise the towering set, which includes an LED display and audible countdown to the race launch.

Marbles race one another in twin speedways
Hundreds of colorful construction pieces
Sound effects, including countdown to race launch

Compete against friends or bogeymen bored of scaring you
Recommended for ages 8 and up
Requires two AA batteries (not included)

This Marble Race set is pretty cool, but has some significant flaws.  None of the pieces really fit together all that well and need to be adjusted pretty frequently.  Kinder Playtime rates this toy a 3 out of 5 KP rating.

Barbie - a doll manufactured by Mattel, one of the best-selling toys and at the same time the most well-known icons of mass culture.
Barbie was created by Ruth Handler in 1958 based on adult German doll Lilli. Barbie made her debut on the New York toy market on March 9, 1959, after purchasing the rights to Lilli by Mattel, founded by Ruth and Elliott Handler.
The name Barbie is a diminutive from the name of the daughter of Ruth Handler, Barbara, for whom Ruth bought a copy of Lilli while in Switzerland. The full name of the doll is Barbara Millicent Roberts. It is only part of an invented biography, in which there are, among others, boy Barbie - Ken and her friends - Midge and Teresa. tags: slime,slick slime sam,easy crafts,fun crafts,DIY,Do it yourself,crafts,diy projects,Tutorial,hot glue,candy,toy,compilation,scruff a luvs,little live pets,scruff a luv,toy review,toy unboxing,pet rescue,bunny,limited edition,scruff,stuffed animal,blossom bunnies,unboxing,grooming,cute animals,blind box,mystery,surprise,surprise toys,purple,yellow,lemon drizzle,play,pets,scruffy,blue,pink,kitten,puppy,funny
description:
UNBELIEVABLE STORIES OF LITTLE LIVE PETS! Find and rescue little cute critters, wash and groom, enjoy having adorable fluffy friends!



Funny little Scruff-A-Luv pets are taking over the world and kids' hearts all over the world! Are you one of us? Don't worry if you don't have one of these cuties yet! Specially for you we are unboxing four adorable little stuffed animals!

Each of them comes in a cute little box and there are so many mystery treasures inside! First, you'll see a little ball of fur that doesn't look like anything. The only feature worth meantioning in this little guys are his giant sad eyes! And maybe color, Scruff-A-Luvs come in the most pretty pastel colors like baby blue, light pink, lav ender and sunny yellow. Put this furball aside for now and look at the rest. There's a collar with a name tag for your pet, a beautiful hair brush (or is it a fur brush?), a hair clip and an adoption certificate. Excited yet?

There's also a detailed step-by-step instruction on how to make this scruffy guy into a soft pet friend for you. First, you want to wash it. We don't normally use shampoo or soap but it's totally ok to do so. Once wet your pet will start to take shape and you'll find out if you got a little bunny, a kitty or a doggy. Then you'll need to groom your pet and dry its fur. Slick Slime Sam loves grooming our pets so I usually trust him with this task. Then name your little live pet and put his name on a name tag, l put on an accessory and have fun together!



0:10 - üíôRESCUING BLUE SCRUFF-A-LUV

I found this little dirty ball of fur on the street. What is it and what do I do to rescue it?

4:49 - üíóUNPACKING PINK SCRUFF A LUV

Now I found an abandoned pet right in front of our door! Who would do such a thing?

9:08 - üíúOPENING PURPLE SCRUFFY PET TOY

We fell in love with Scruff A Luvs and bought an extra cute purple buddy!

14:46 - üíõUNBOXING LIMITED EDITION YELLOW SCRUFF A LOVE

Is that a blossom bunny among the lemons? We need to rescue it!

title: Electric Motors Explained - 50 Year Old Toy Unboxing
tags: Electric Motor (Engine Category),motor,motors,electric,electrical,armature,commutator,rotor,stator,field,windings,field windings,generator,genny,genset,starter,magnetic,electro-magnet,Energy,Electric Generator (Invention),toy,toys,kit,kits,kid,kids,educational,learn,tutorial,lesson,explanation,repairs,repairs101,repairs101ca,unbox,unboxing,Electricity (Industry),demonstration
description:
Unboxing a 1965 Science Kit and assembling a DC Electric Motor while explaining the components that make it work.
Transcript provided for the hearing impaired:
Alright so today on Repairs101 -- I've got this science kit from 1965 -- still in its original box -- that I'm going to open and assemble and use to explain all the different components of an electric motor and how one works.
I'm unboxing a fifty year old kids' toy that most kids would find pointless and boring because understanding how an electric motor works will unlock the secret of how literally millions of different machines work; machines that you use and ride on everyday. 
This invention is widely used because of its versatility -- it can be made small enough to drive the hands on the tiniest wristwatches and big and heavy enough to drive the wheels on the heaviest of heavy equipment.
The coils are all wound clockwise so that the magnetic fields are consistent.
The motor exploits the concept of magnetic attraction and repulsion and the forces of nature are put to work using rotating and stationary electro-magnets.
As the rotor spins, each commutator comes in and out of contact with the power circuit through the brushes. 
The stator is an electro-magnet that is energized at the same time as the rotor. 
As for all you thinking girls and boys who are going to go on to become engineers and industrial designers -- remember this machine. It runs completely clean. Don't forget.
Alright, thanks for watching and don't forget to subscribe!

Cars is a 2006 American computer-animated comedy-adventure sports film produced by Pixar Animation Studios and released by Walt Disney Pictures. Directed and co-written by John Lasseter, it is Pixar's final independently-produced motion picture before its purchase by Disney. Set in a world populated entirely by anthropomorphic cars and other vehicles, it features the voices of Owen Wilson, Paul Newman (in his final non-documentary feature), Larry the Cable Guy, Bonnie Hunt, Tony Shalhoub, Cheech Marin, Michael Wallis, George Carlin, Paul Dooley, Jenifer Lewis, Guido Quaroni, Michael Keaton, Katherine Helmond, and John Ratzenberger. Real life race car drivers Dale Earnhardt, Jr., Mario Andretti and Michael Schumacher, and car enthusiast Jay Leno (as "Jay Limo") voice themselves. It is also the second Pixar film‚Äîafter A Bug's Life‚Äîto have an entirely non-human cast. The film was accompanied by the short One Man Band for its theatrical and home media releases. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cars_(film)

PJ Masks is about three 6-year-olds, Connor, Amaya, and Greg, who lead relatively normal lives by day, where they are neighbors, classmates, and friends. However, at night, they put on their pyjamas and become Catboy, Owlette, and Gekko, and fight crime as the superhero team PJ Masks. Together, they go on adventures, defeat villains, solve mysteries, and learn valuable lessons. Catboy has super-hearing using Cat Ears, can leap high and far using Super Cat Jump, and sprints fast using Super Cat Speed.  Gecko can use Super Gekko Camouflage to change colors and blend in with his surroundings, Super Gekko Muscles (aka Super Muscles) to lift heavy things, Super Lizard Grip to climb walls or anchor himself to stop vehicles, and Super Lizard Water Run to walk on water. Owlette is able to see in the dark using Owl Eyes (or Super Owl Eyes) and fly by using Super Owl Wings, which she can also use to launch gusts of air to send opponents flying backward,[8] which she calls her Owl Wing Wind.

title: #35 Switch Adapted Toys 1 of 2: Exercises for a Child with Cerebral Palsy
tags: Sebastian,Amy Sturkey,Pediatric,Physical Therapy,Paediatric,physiotherapy,Occupational Therapy,child,#pediPT,#PedsPT,cerebral palsy,disability,physically challenged,physically handicapped,severe involvement,profound involvement,spastic,spasticity,quadriplegic,quadriplegia,stiffness,#cp,#cerebralpalsy,#cpwarrior,#cpstrong,#specialneeds,#cerebralpalsykids,#specialneedskids,#cerebralpalsyawareness,#disabilityawareness,PT,OT,#pediOT,#PedsOT,sitting,reaching,switch adapted,toy
description:
Meet Sebastian. He is a young boy with Spastic Quadriplegic Cerebral Palsy. His family wants to help me share treatment suggestions to help children like him across the world.  My clinic, Child and Family Development,  in Charlotte, NC, allowed me to use their facilities and their equipment to showcase Sebastian's skill and charming personality. We review techniques to reduce stiffness, encourage strength and control. I think you'll love spending time with him. Thank you to this family and my clinic for allowing this to happen.
 I also have available 3 children's educational books, "A is for Autism," "D is for Down Syndrome," "C is for Cerebral Palsy,"   and now 2 professional books "Pediatric Physical Therapy Exercises for the Hips", and "Pediatric Physical Therapy Exercises for the Knees" available on Amazon.  I have forthcoming "A is for ADHD" as well.  If you have questions or suggestions, feel free to contact me at amysturkey@gmail.com. Please note: I am unable to provide treatment suggestions for a child I have not personally evaluated.
I am so honored to have people from all over the world watch my videos. I have reviewed and corrected the closed captions for this video so that you might understand what I am saying even if you don't speak English. I hope the directions below are helpful to you. 
To turn on Captions, click CC in the bottom right corner of the video
To choose a different caption language:
At the bottom right, click Settings. It looks like a wheel.
Click Subtitles/CC.
Select a language.
If the language isn't listed when you click Subtitles/CC:
Click Auto-translate.
Select a language.

description:
This is an Unboxing and Review of the HEXBUG Nano Nitro Habitat Set as a part of my latest Kids Toy Review series. It shows me demonstrating how to work HEXBUG Nano Nitro it came with along with the five more, plus a HEXBUG Nano V2 Robot Bug that came with  the HEXBUG Nano V2 Neon Infinity Loop Set.

Here are the pros & cons for this HEXBUG Toy Set:

Pros:

- The HEXBUG kit goes together quickly and easily
- You can configure the track parts and pieces in a variety of ways
- Parts and pieces from other HEXBUG playsets can be added
- The more HEXBUGS you add, the more action packed fun
- You can adjust the different hex platforms flags to change how they interact with the HEXBUGS

Cons:
- I honestly don't see any! It is a great value and lots of fun!

Be sure to look at my recent videos for the HEXBUG Ring Racer Stunt Park, HEXBUG Soccer Arena, Nerf Blaster Reviews, and fun toys like Flarp.

On the Nerf Gun or Nerf Blaster side of things, be sure to click that subscribe button and click on the bell to make sure you don't miss any of the fun coming up like my reviews of the Zuru X-Shot Turbo Fire Blaster and Zuru X-Shot Fast Fill Water Gun! Also, don't forget to check out my latest reviews of the Nerf Revreaper & the Zuru X-Shot Fury 4 dart gun.

This is how HEXBUG describes this Toy Kit:

"This playset unlocks the world of the nano robotic creature as it allows you to create customizable playgrounds for these industrious critters to explore. Featuring simple snap-together pieces, your imagination is the limit.

The nano are tiny micro robotic creatures that once switched on, can skitter their way through any maze. Watch as it travels swiftly around curves, zooms through merry-go-rounds, or chases a fellow nano Nitro in a high-speed race! Designed to foster children‚Äôs creativity, develop fine-motor skills, and fuel hours of amusement, this set gets kids to think about simple construction techniques as well as the science behind the toy.

HEXBUG nano Nitro Habitat Set is compliant with CPSIA standards.

Discover an all new realm of creative fun, with the HEXBUG Nano Nitro Habitat Set.
- 30+ easy connect pieces
- One nano Nitro included

- Vibration technology

We‚Äôre super excited to unbox a huge haul of new Toy Story 4 toys. There are toys from Mattel, Lego, Thinkway Toys, Disney and more.  

The RV Friends 6 Pack is perfect for fans who want to instantly build their Toy Story 4 collection. It includes Woody, Buzz, Forky,  Rex, Slinky, Jessie.

Who wouldn‚Äôt want to create their own Forky? We found this Creativity Craft set.  With pipe cleaners, Play-Doh, and googly eyes. It allows you to make your own DIY Forky just like Bonnie. 

Bo Peep is a part of the True Talkers line, which feature 15 phrases. Press the button on her belt to hear her talk. It‚Äôs so fun to see what she will say. 

Here‚Äôs the Benson and Woody 2-Pack.  The coolest part? You can press the button on his head to make him talk just like a real dummy. It comes with a special movie edition of Woody.  

Here‚Äôs a couple of new friends that we won as carnival prizes - it‚Äôs Ducky and Bunny, played by the humorous duo of Key and Peele.

Look it‚Äôs Woody‚Äôs horse - Bullseye! He comes in this special edition Woody & Bullseye Adventure Pack. 

Both figures can be posed on their own or together. 
Wisecracking piggy bank, Hamm is here. What‚Äôs cool? He‚Äôs a real piggy bank! 
Three aliens from the strange world of Pizza Planet also arrived on our doorstep. 
From the Disney Store, we picked up plush figures of Dolly ,Mr. Pricklepants, Buttercup,and Trixie. 

If you didn‚Äôt think that the Toy Story 4 toys could get any cuter, check out the minis. 
If you‚Äôve ever wanted Buzz Lightyear with all the features from the commercial, check out the Special Edition of Talking Buzz Lightyear. 

Wearing 80‚Äôs-inspired workout gear, Barbie‚Äôs ready for a workout. 
Mattel has taken the essence of all our favorite characters and turned them into cars. Aren‚Äôt these awesome?! Characters in the line include Woody, Buzz. Alien, Rex, and more.

With Stunt Racer Duke Caboom can bring home Duke Caboom.  He‚Äôs the most spectacular daredevil that Canada has ever seen.

We got this Forky & Duke Caboom 2-Pack from Amazon.  Poor Duke - he can‚Äôt perform any of the stunts he‚Äôs advertised to do. 

With his cape and helmet, Duke Caboom looks similar to the standalone figure, and he has all the same articulation. The biggest downside? You can‚Äôt take off his helmet. What‚Äôs great is you can use the standalone figure with this set. 

Bo Peep‚Äôs back! Now you can capture all her fancy moves from the movie with Epic Moves Bo Peep. 

Lastly, we‚Äôve got a Lego set. Designed for ages 4 and up, Buzz & Woody‚Äôs Carnival Mania set recreates the carnival scene inspired by Toy Story 4. 

These are just a few of the new Toy Story 4 toys. It‚Äôs not everything. Check out our Toy Hunt for even more toys.

description:
New Furby Christmas #1 Toy Funny Interactive Teach & Learn Kids Toys by Toy Review TV.
Who will your Furby become? It all depends on how you play with your Furby. So when you are feeding, tickling, shaking, tilting or turning it, pulling its tail, speaking to it or playing music for it, keep in mind that your actions will shape its personality. Play nicely with Furby and it may develop a sweet personality, but, pull its tail, shake and turn it upside down and a mischievous side of Furby may appear.
Furby has a mind of its own. You see, Furby has likes and dislikes just like you. You will discover them as you and Furby get to know one another. Furby will express its emotions to you in a variety of ways, expressive LED eyes are just one of many ways. Furby may not react or behave the way you expect or the way you want, so you may be happy about some of its reactions and not so happy about others.
There is something you should know about Furby. Furby can be unpredictable. Be careful how you treat Furby. Who your Furby becomes may surprise you. So, are you ready to handle a Furby?
Furby can also recognise another Furby, place two side by side and they will interact, including dancing together or having a conversation. Introduce your Furby to other Furbys and see what happens. Again, you never know how your Furby will react, so it may get along well with some Furbys and may have a bad attitude with others.
When you first meet your Furby, it will speak Furbish. But the more you play with Furby, the more English it will start speaking. Not sure what your Furby is saying? Do all those ee-tays and noo-loos have you scratching your head? Then check out the complete Furbish dictionary at www.Furby.com or in the free Furby app to translate Furbish into English and find out what Furby is talking about.
Feed your Furby. Give your Furby food by using the Furby app that lets you virtually feed your Furby: Feed it a hot pepper and you may see fire in its eyes. Try different foods and see how it responds.
Additional Information
For additional interactive Furby fun, owners can download the free Furby App for iPhone, iPad, and iPod touch, available at the App store. Use your Furby app to virtually feed your Furby, access a Furbish to English dictionary and use the Furbish to English translator.

Sky Organics Kids Bath Bombs gift box contains 6 super-sized bath bombs which were handcrafted with love in the USA. 
They each contain a "Suprise Toy" when they fizz out. Currently featuring gender neutral "Pokemon" Toys.

Settle in for a wonderful immersion with an original Sky Organics invention,exploding with  essential oils, coconut oil and tons of fizzy fun. Our Kids bath bombs offer a fun multilayered explosion of color and scent.
They also contain "bath sprinkles" that make the water sparkle.

Utilizing only the finest natural and organic ingredients our bath bombs will leave the skin hydrated and moisturized.
They are Kid Safe. (WARNING: chocking hazard-not for children under the age of 3)

Six Assorted Scents:
Bubble Gum :- Sweet & juicy childhood bubblegum (pink and white)
Cotton Candy: Fabulous aroma of freshly spun cotton candy. A blend of fresh strawberry and French vanilla.(blue and fuscia)
Dreamsicle: A refreshing iced orange popsicle with a creamy vanilla filling! (orange and white)
Galaxy: Reach for the stars- Lemon rinds, lime, and grapefruit; middle notes of lemongrass, lily, and verbena; and base notes of vanilla sugar.. (black and blue)
Grape Soda: Effervescent aroma of Kyoho grapes intermingled with fresh peaches, pineapple, raspberries, and strawberries on a dry down of vanilla. (purple and white)
Gummy Bear: A childhood favorite, the essence of chewy gummy candy bursting with fruity goodness ! (green and blue)

description:
You will never guess what someone put in a squishy package‚Ä¶.WAIT FOR IT.

SO YES. Today is a SUPER long squishy unboxing video because I am opening 50 packages! I know it‚Äôs a LOT and this video goes on forever. But, I hope you enjoy it. All these packages have been building up and taking over the space in my apartment. So I needed a way to get through a lot very quickly so I could start putting things away. I know I said not everyone would be featured on camera (since most of these were sent after my announcements that I have closed donations), BUT I feel bad because I know these took time, effort and money. After this batch, I am not going to push myself so hard to include every single one. These unboxings will become less frequent, since I am moving to every other Monday. I will probably only post these once every month from now on and I will have to pick and choose packages that get featured in the videos.  

______FOR THE NEW COMERS (if I didn‚Äôt already scare you away)________
A couple of months ago, I started this series called ‚ÄúSquishy Makeovers.‚Äù I was using ugly, cheap squishies and then painting them, adding to them and fixing them up however I saw fit. That series became a new favorite on my channel, and I decided to allow subscribers to participate by donating their own ugly, used, broken or unwanted squishies. At the time, I had a much smaller audience, but quickly my channel grew and I became overwhelmed with tons of squishy packages.  I am still working on catching up with all the packages I have received in the last few months. I have spent 4 entire videos unboxing squishy donations, and this is the biggest batch so far. Everyone comments on these videos, which squishies they want to see in the makeover videos (4 candidates), and I give the most popular requests a makeover in the next makeover video (every other Friday). These pacakages are donation only, from people who no longer want the squishies or are just interested in seeing them on camera. The squishies are not returned to the sender after the makeovers. If that doesn‚Äôt make sense, I made a video to explain. I‚Äôd appreciate if you checked it out: 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gKYCVbM8RU4&t=101s

*ATTENTION*
The P.O. Box address in this video is no longer open!!! I no longer have a P.O. box in this location, so any mail sent to this address will be automatically returned to sender. Check out this video for updates:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qfLxIrfLjFc&t=10s


VIDEO FACTS:
1. this took 4.5 hours to film the in front of the camera part, 2 hours to film all the close up shots of each package, and an hour to clean up haha
2. I was editing this from 9am-3am Tuesday. 11am-5pm Wednesday. And then from 10am-5pm on Thursday. It was about 26 HOURS OF EDITING.
3. This is the first time in MONTHS I have had my Friday video done before Friday! YAYYYY!

description:
The kids learning how to hang upside down üòÇ
and YOUR MERCH IS BACK!!   http://aforadley.com/

JOIN OUR FAM!! --- http://goo.gl/rfgp8V

Best Daredevil Day Ever 1155

One of the families favorite things about October is all of the Halloween decorations. Jenny, Adley and Niko Bear found some awesome bats that go perfect for the holiday and decide to hang them on the door. Adley, being the loving little girl that she is, groups them in families and names them after all of us. 

Once the door is all decorated, the find me downstairs so they can show me the great job that they did. After decorations, Adley comes up with a brand new game called statue! the rules are easy, Adley and Niko are statues, Jenny sells them, and I buy them. But they are crazy. The Adley statue moves around when I'm not looking while the Niko Bear statue has a button to make it come a live and run around the room. haha I love pretend play with the kiddos!!

With the new game done, I have to show you guys a new trick that the kiddos and I learned. We can hang from the ceiling in the kitchen!! It's hilarious, though Jenny wishes we didn't use the house like a park toy. We then head to the backyard splash pad to find some rocks for arts and crafts time.

We love doing little DIY creative projects with the kiddos, but these are extra special, because we are going to take these rocks to the construction site of a brand new LDS Temple. These temples are super important to us, so its awesome that we get to put little memories into the foundation. Adley draws pretty flowers, Niko colors his rock so good, and Jenny makes a cute rock for her and baby Navey and I make a rock about our family and how much we love each other. ( Also with a little pirate theme for pirate island lol)

After dropping of the rocks and doing some work at the lake lot, I'm home for the night! I also brought gifts for the whole family. We have A for Adley shirts again!! We have a brand new company making them and they look so good. The colors are bright, the images look great, and we are excited to share them with you guys again!! Prices are still the same, we want them to be easy for you to get. If you bought a shirt before and there were problems with it, we want to help. After unboxing the surprise, it's time to start our bed time routine and end this amazing Best Day Ever!!

Product Description

A radio-controlled aircraft (often called RC aircraft or RC plane) is a small flying machine that is controlled remotely by an operator on the ground using a hand-held radio transmitter. The transmitter communicates with a receiver within the craft that sends signals to servomechanisms (servos) which move the control surfaces based on the position of joysticks on the transmitter. The control surfaces, in turn, affect the orientation of the plane.

Flying RC aircraft as a hobby grew substantially from the 2000s with improvements in the cost, weight, performance and capabilities of motors, batteries and electronics. A wide variety of models and styles is available.

Scientific, government and military organizations are also using RC aircraft for experiments, gathering weather readings, aerodynamic modeling and testing. Unmanned aerial vehicle (drones) or spy planes add video or autonomous capabilities, and may be armed.[1]

Get your own Backyard Bass Casting Game for Kids on Amazon.com here: http://www.amazon.com/dp/B0007IQAIG/?tag=connorscorner-20

Connor and his dad join up in this video for the first time.  They play the game first over concrete.  Then they try and get adventurous and go into the water... but the fish gets blown to the other side of the lake!   

Backyard Bass is a fishing game that helps kids learn and practice how to cast.  It uses a weighted plug, so there are no dangerous, sharp fishing hooks while learning.  It can be used on a flat surface or in the water like a pool or lake (but don't let your fish get blown away!) 

There are different sized sets from 3 to 16 for larger groups or just more fish to catch if you are casting over a large area. This toy game is especially for those aged 6 and up.

title: Unboxing The "L.O.L. Surprise! Big Surprise" ‚Äî The Hottest Toy Of 2017
tags: Tech Insider,TI,Tech,Science,Innovation,Digital culture,Design,Technology,Unboxing,L.O.L. Surprise,MGA Entertainment,Toys,Toy trends,Trends,Holiday,Shopping,Retail,Holiday trends,Hatchimal
description:
In 2016, every kid wanted a Hatchimal, and parents were running around coughing up lots of money to make sure their child got one. This year, the hot toy for the holidays is something called the "L.O.L. Surprise! Big Surprise," a giant, glittery ball packed with 50 smaller toys that kids can unwrap. It sells for $69.99, but if you can manage to find one, you'll probably be paying a lot more. They're going for over $100 on eBay. When it was first released in September, it sold out within 48 hours at most stores. The company behind the toy, MGA Entertainment, even encourages kids to "unbox" the gift and post videos on YouTube. Do a quick search, and you'll see how popular they are for yourself. We got ahold of one of the toys to see what exactly you are getting for your money. Following is a transcript of the video.

This is the "L.O.L. Surprise! Big Surprise."

It's a bowl-shaped plastic container with 50 toy "surprises" inside. Including dolls, stickers, and accessories. 

Kids are encouraged to film unboxing videos of it. There are thousands of them already on YouTube.

The $69.99 toy is sold out at most retailers, and it's selling for more than $100 on eBay. 

We got our hands on one to show you what's inside.

There's an instruction manual and a scratch-off card to win a prize online. 

The first layer contains 10 individual capsules. These contain tiny items of clothing. Here's everything we got in our capsules.

The second layer has 5 "fizz" balls with 15 items. Unwrapping each one reveals two stickers. Removing another layer exposes the fizz ball.  Each dissolves in water to reveal a plastic charm.

The final layer has 4 balls with 24 items total. The two smaller balls are marked "Lil Sisters." Inside each ball are more packets to open.

There's a small doll inside one pack. The other packs contain items like bags and shoes.

The two larger balls each have 7 items inside. Inside are items like cell phones and cups.

Each has a larger doll with some unique features. They cry, spit, tinkle, or change color in water.

It will take a while to open everything inside, and you will have lots of trash to clean up.

description:
Unboxing Chuggington StackTrack a stackable toy for kids with the Chuggington train. This toy set of Chungington features Koko, the green train. With super slow motion video footage.
In this unboxing video for kids we will find the Chuggington StackTrack a Working WheelsService Yard Set with Koko Lola, which is the official name for this Chuggington toy set. Jus like Thomas and Friends this is a great toy for kids.

This Chunggington train toy set is very similar to the Thomas and friends trains, it includes tracks and a ramp, where Koko can perform jumps! Have you ever seen trains jump? This stackable train track lets kids learn and build their own train tracks. It can be customized in unlimited ways and this box includes the green train called Koko.

Koko Lola train is an electric engine train. She is a little bit green and purple and she was built for really high speeds. That makes her one of the fastest Chuggers in Chuggington she love adventures and in this toys set she will even jump!
Kids know Chunggington from the disney cartoons aired on Nickelodeon and Nick Jr and Disney Junior tv channels. This Chuggington StackTrack we're unboxing in this video for kids is appropriate for children of 3 years and up. Launch Koko and jump! This kids train set of chungington is great fun to play with. Connect this set to other Stack 

Track sets of Chunggington. For example if you already have Brewster and Wilson which are the other advanced trainees. The chuggers and trainees of chinggington are waiting for you to build some train tracks. Watch this fun kids video on youtube and see what the chungington train stack track looks like. If you've seen the Disney junior chuggington cartoons, then you'll probably like this unboxing video too.

Be sure to like our video and subscribe to see more!

description:
Unboxing Smart Shots Sports Center! Toddler play and learn with sports toys, basketball and soccer action!

Nessa is a natural she takes over and starts slamming the basketball in the basket, I see a lot of promise for this one year old in her sports skills.

Nate gets all excited about unboxing the toy set, he has seen so many youtube unboxing toys videos that for him to experience it in real life really is something for him.  

We all start testing out this playset and throwing the basketball and soccer ball trying to make shot, our sports skills are rusty but it was still good family fun testing out this toy. 

The interactive learning part of the set is great, there are all type of knobs and buttons for the kids to explore and learn their numbers and ABCs while playing.  

The set was really easy to put together, came right out of the box.  Only technical part was using a screwdriver to open the batter box but that was really easy.

Overall this is a great kids toy for toddlers, as it is aimed to that age group for learning and playing.  We love Vtech toys and have lots of different sets even before making any videos, so they are very popular toys.

Our magical sun gives gardens and farms the light and warmth they need to grow the ingredients that go into all our favourite foods. Kyra's unboxing the super fun Jungle Magic Garden Sciencz experiment kit to show you how food grows!

Kyra is eagerly waiting for her "food to start growing" on her plants, she checks on them every five minutes! If you have a curious little person in your life, we suggest you get them this kit too to arouse some hunger for observing nature as well as appreciation for patient practice of gardening.

description:
Halo sahabat, Mudah-mudahan sehat selalu ya :)

Video kali ini menampilkan beberapa mainan kendaraan Yaitu Pesawat Jet, Helikopter, Kapal Perang dan Pesawat Terbang.  

1. Pesawat terbang adalah Mainan kendaraan sejenis Pesawat Airbus yang bertipe mainan RC (Remote Control)
2. StarwarShip adalah jenis mainan yang dapat berubah dari pesawat jet menjadi robot dan sebaliknya
3. Forest Helikopter Adalah Mainan Kendaraan yang bertenaga baterai dan jika aslinya diperuntukan untuk menjelajahi wilayah hutan
4. Marine Patrol Boat adalah Mainan sejenis Kendaraan Perang yang juga bertenaga baterai dan jika aslinya adalah biasa digunakan diwilayah laut terutama di perbatasan laut antar negara untuk mengontol jika ada pelanggaran wilayah kedaulatan laut dan juga mencegah pencurian ikan (Ilegal Fishing)

Mudah-mudahan keterangan diatas dapat bermanfaat untuk semua, terutama ibu dan balita indonesia yang sedang belajar nama kendaraan baik itu kendaraan di udara dan dilaut, belajar berhitung dan juga warna, baik dalam bahasa indonesia dan bahasa inggris

Always wear appropriate safety equipment.  Exercise caution and common sense ‚Äì do not assume you can easily to everything you may see on a video, because all trick or aggressive riding takes practice and involves increased risks.  Always check local laws regarding use of electric-powered products.

‚ù§ Description ‚ù§

Once more, we have Play Doh featured in a play set! These kinds of toy sets which use plasticine are always a great hit, as most kids really like to use play dough, considering it is absolutely great for developing creativity and imagination. The contents of this modeling clay for children, it seems, is a secret well kept, although we can tell that this is a dough for modeling various figures and characters as well as a sundry of objects, and contains both water and salt, as well as flour and wheat. We also need to say that this putty for playing has no peanuts or dairy products and that these kinds of toy sets are non-toxic, non-allergenic, and do not produce any irritation. It is also a great advantage that this dough can be used time and time again. And last but not least, it is definitely not a foodstuff!

And what is this play set about? It features Stitch from the Lilo and Stitch franchise films. Stitch is a so-called genetic experiment, an alien who looks like a blue koala bear. This is a character which is liked by no one expect for Lilo, who refers to him as a dog. In fact, he has superhuman strength and a very high IQ but he behaves like a child. This play set includes 5 boxes of Play Dough surprises. The first box with blue plasticine features the figure of Stitch with a wobbly head eating a cupcake. The next one, with red play dough, is Stitch sitting on a doughnut. The third, in yellow play dough, is the figure of Stitch with an ice cream cone in his hand. The fourth box contains blue play clay and a figure of Stitch and a mug of cocoa. And the penultimate box contains burnt orange clay with Stitch eating candy. And last but in no way least, the purple Play Doh, after being taken off, will display Stitch eating cake.

Rusty Rivets is a Canadian CGI interactive animated television series produced by Arc Productions and Spin Master Entertainment for Treehouse TV and Nickelodeon Productions. Inspired by elements of the maker culture, it follows the adventures of a young inventor named Rusty and his team of customized robots. A boy named Rusty Rivets uses his knowledge of engineering to repurpose machine parts and create gadgets. He lives in the city of Sparkton Hills along with his friend Ruby Ramirez, a robotic tyrannosaurid named Botasaur, and a group of smaller robots known as the Bits. The show highlights a variety of concepts related to basic science and technology.

Rusty uses the recurring catch phrase "modify, customize, Rustify" when personalizing inventions. Ruby changes the last word to "Rubify" when she does the alterations.

description:
Watch Thomas complete his most breathtaking stunt yet in the Thomas and Friends TrackMaster Sky-High Bridge Jump from Fisher-Price. This Thomas & Friends train set breaks new ground by taking Thomas off the tracks and sending him soaring through the air, delivering speed, excitement, and motorized action like only TrackMaster train sets can! Inspired by the Thomas & Friends DVD, The Great Race, Sky-High Bridge Jump brings the movie to life with fast-paced, flying thrills. After a tall, spiral ascent with Harold the helicopter, Thomas speeds down a huge ramp and the velocity launches him into the air! Thomas soars for over two feet (0,6 meters) through the air before landing safely on the other side and continuing his journey. This one-of-a-kind Thomas & Friends train set also features a cargo hopper, waving flags, a barrel cargo piece, and removable Harold the helicopter.
- Complete Thomas & Friends train set includes motorized Thomas train, Harold the helicopter, cargo hopper, cargo piece, and full track layout with ramp and bridge jump
- Send Thomas under the bridge and up the spiral track
- When Thomas reaches the end of the track, Harold will lift him to the top of the ramp
- Thomas lands safely and continues his journey around the rails
- Tip the hopper to drop the barrel onto the tracks and Thomas will push it into the cargo area

Please Subscribe Here http://www.youtube.com/user/TheEngineeringFamily?sub_confirmation=1

The Disney Junior Mickey Mouse Clubhouse Doctor Kit is a way for your Mickey Mouse Fan into a doctor. There are similar Disney Junior Doc McStuffins Doctor kits, but this one is definitely designed for a Mickey Mouse fan.

Notes-

- Comes with a battery operated stethoscope. The stethoscope is probably the highlight of the set.

- Has a thermometer for checking temperature - each time you click the thermometer you change the temperature on its display.

- A small flashlight is included for checking throats and ears

- The blood pressure cuff doesn't pump with air.... unlike the one that comes with the Doc mcStuffins playset

- Has a small mirror

- A few other items are included like two band aids

Final Verdict - Our daughter prefers the Mickey Mouse Clubhouse Doctor kit over-and-above the one from Doc McStuffins. She prefers the blood pressure cuff from Doc McStuffins but she likes all of the additional doctor tools in the Mickey kit.

4 1/2 Stars

PJ Masks is about three 6-year-olds, Connor, Amaya, and Greg, who lead relatively normal lives by day, where they are neighbors, classmates, and friends. However, at night, they put on their pyjamas and become Catboy, Owlette, and Gekko, and fight crime as the superhero team PJ Masks. Together, they go on adventures, defeat villains, solve mysteries, and learn valuable lessons. Catboy has super-hearing using Cat Ears, can leap high and far using Super Cat Jump, and sprints fast using Super Cat Speed.  Gecko can use Super Gekko Camouflage to change colors and blend in with his surroundings, Super Gekko Muscles (aka Super Muscles) to lift heavy things, Super Lizard Grip to climb walls or anchor himself to stop vehicles, and Super Lizard Water Run to walk on water. Owlette is able to see in the dark using Owl Eyes (or Super Owl Eyes) and fly by using Super Owl Wings, which she can also use to launch gusts of air to send opponents flying backward,[8] which she calls her Owl Wing Wind.

description:
LEGO Chima 70146 Flying Phoenix Fire Temple Toy Review & Unboxing

It's the ultimate fire vs. ice showdown as the Saber-tooth warriors attack the all-powerful Phoenix tribe's Fire Temple. Can they capture the great Phoenix leader Fluminox and his CHI and take control of the entire Kingdom of Chima? Behind the gates, there's a pool of fire balls and an array of red-hot weaponry to put the heat on the invaders. Help Flinx defend the Temple from the gun turret and unleash the fire bombs. Act quickly before the Saber-tooth vehicle breaks down the Temple walls with its powerful clawing function. Or activate fire CHI power mode to convert part of the temple into a huge flying Phoenix, taking the thrilling action to the sky against the ejected Saber-tooth flyer! 

Includes 7 minifigures with weapons: Fluminox, Flinx, Foltrax, Tormak, Li'Ella, Stealthor and Voom Voom
Phoenix Fire Temple features base opening/closing function, load-and-fire bombing feature, 2 gun turrets with gun sight and seats for minifigures, opening gate, pool of fire balls and translucent flame elements, plus fire CHI power mode flying Phoenix with fire CHI, ball shooters, load-and-fire bombing feature and phoenix detailing
Saber-tooth vehicle features clawing function, CHI, ball shooter, ice fangs, claws and tail plus detachable flyer with posable wings
Weapons include a Wingfurno for Fluminox, Flikker for Flinx, Emberstaf for Foltrax, Tygafyre for Tormak, Roarburn for Li'Ella, Koldstaf for Stealthor and a Double Axicles for Voom Voom
Place Phoenix minifigures in the gun turret seats and target the invaders
Unleash the fire bombs
Enter fire CHI power mode to convert part of the Temple into a flying Phoenix!
Claw the temple wall with the Saber-tooth vehicle
Detach the Saber-tooth flyer and shoot the ice orbs
Phoenix Fire Temple measures over 6" (16cm) high, 17" (44cm) long and 18" (46cm) wide, and over 3" (10cm) high, 15" (39cm) long and 17" (45cm) wide in fire-up mode
2-in-1 Saber-tooth vehicle measures over 6" (16cm) high, 8" (21cm) long and 4" (12cm) wide
Saber-tooth detachable flyer measures over 2" (6cm) high, 9" (23cm) long and 7" (18cm) wide

title: TRANSFORMERS CRASH COMBINER FORCE WAVE 3 SHOCKNADO DRAGBREAK TOY UNBOXING REVIEW RID
tags: Transformers,Transformers combiner force,Shocknado,Dragbreak,wave 3,toys,crash combiners,transformers robots in disguise,optimus prime,bumblebee,megatron,1 step changers,autobots,decepticons,transformers: the last knight trailer,#transformers,transformers RID,robots in disguise,combiner force,#hasbro,transformers 2017,Transformers topic,transformers toys,toytimetv,toy reviews,shockdrive,Warnado,Dragstrip,Wildbreak,RID,strongarm,sideswipe,cartoon network,episode
description:
Transformers RID Combiner Force wave 3 has been released! The Transformers Robots in Disguise crash combers are so cool. In this RID comber force brand toy review episode we have crash combiner Dragbreak, who is combiner force of the decepticons Dragestrip and Wildbreak, and Shocknado, who is a combiner force of Shockdrive and Warnado. You can mix them up to create DRAGNADO with dragstrip and warnado and SHOCKBREAK with Shockdrive and Warnado. You can even combine the other Combine Force to make Autobot Decepticon robots to make PrimeDrag and Beeshock and all kinds of other crazy combinations in the Transformer universe. These one step transformer and Robots in disguise are so awesome! Mr Hands got mixed up on the names of Shockdrive and Warnado and Bobby thought it was really funny. Hr Hands needs to learn his Transformer RID name better. Transformers are so much fun to play with and use your imagination to pretend like you are on cartoon network.
